headline: CNN Live Event/Special
subHeadline: New Year's Eve Live With Andy Cohen And Anderson Cooper CNN Special. Aired 8-9p ET

utterances.speaker: BORIS SANCHEZ, CNN HOST
utterances.sentences: Again, shout out to that vaping doctor that hooked me up with all these prescriptions, because I feel pretty good. I think it went pretty well, I've got to say.

utterances.speaker: USHER, AMERICAN SINGER, SONGWRITER, DANCER, ACTOR
utterances.sentences: Yo, what's up Anderson and Andy.JENNIFER GOICOECHEA, USHER'S WIFE: Happy New Year.

utterances.speaker: USHER
utterances.sentences: We're here in Las Vegas at Flipper's Roller Boogie Palace, having a great time.

utterances.speaker: ANNOUNCER
utterances.sentences: From the heart of Time-Square, it's CNN's New Year's Eve live. Welcome to TV's wildest party with performances and appearances by 50 Cent, Jon Hamm, Meghan Trainor, Ralph Fiennes, Shania Twain, Whitney Cummings, Anthony Henderson and his mom, Sting, Ziwe, Lil Jon, Mickey Guyton, the cast of "Have I Got News For You" and more surprises.And now, your hosts Anderson Cooper and Andy Cohen. ANDERSON COOPER, CNN HOST, "ANDERSON COOPER: 360": And welcome to Times Square in the last four hours of 2024. I'm Anderson Cooper here with Andy Cohen in the middle of thousands, tens of thousands, maybe hundreds of thousands of partiers who did not let the threat of rain dampen their spirits or water down their drinks.

utterances.speaker: ANDY COHEN, AMERICAN RADIO AND TELEVISION TALK SHOW HOST, PRODUCER, WRITER
utterances.sentences: Although, by the way, we just walked through.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: They don't seem that psyched. Just so you know, they got to ep it up, everybody. Its New Year's Eve.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: We went to see Sandra Bernhard perform last night, and her crowd was kind of dead, too.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes, exactly. But the earlier crowd was better.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: It's a great show and we have a great show planned tonight. We have a night of music, comedy, alcohol and mayhem. We have so many great guests. I am very excited for this, our eighth year together.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: And they said it wouldn't last.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And they said, it wouldn't last.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I thought you would have been fired by now.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I thought you would have turned on me by now, Anderson.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes, I know, just about 10 minutes ago, Anderson, I thought you were in something of a foul mood.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: The camera seems to have lit you back up. And I'll tell you a moment that you had this year --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: -- which should have put you in a horrible mood. And it's the moment that really, I think, propelled us to where we're about to be. That was you in the hurricane. Look at you getting pounded by debris, Anderson. Look at this clip.(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: It's coming in from down the north, I guess northeast. And the water now is really starting to pour over. If you look at the ground. Whoa, okay that wasn't good.(END VIDEO CLIP)

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: That wasn't good. it was styrofoam, I just want to say, like, there were hundreds of articles the next day saying I was hit in the head by debris.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: None of them said styrofoam, which I pointed out immediately afterward. It was a piece of styrofoam.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Well, you're not implicated in anything. What happened as a result --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I don't know, went crazy. Anderson Cooper is out here getting doinked. Okay, keep going. There's more, there's more. Basically, they felt that after the year that you have had --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: CNN had better let Anderson Cooper blackout on New Year's Eve.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes. Well guess what? That's where I come in. I brought the Tequila, Anderson. I brought the shot glasses.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: But is that -- I've never seen a bottle like that.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I know it's a beautiful bottle. We are going to do this at the top of every hour.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Okay, and we want you to join us. And you can join us with toast. With whatever you're drinking, water --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: And for the record, I do not really drink.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Well, I know, but that's the fun of New Year's Eve. Anderson doesn't drink.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Well, no, it's part of it. Here --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: We are going to have a toast. And this is our virtual celebration. Whether you are at home alone or with family or with one other person, we are all here together. This is an incredible community that we've built up together over these eight years. And so, I am excited. And you know what? I'm starting with a big one.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I know, I'm a little edgy right now.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: All right, thank you. All right, well, Happy New Year.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Okay, Happy New Year, everybody. First toast of the night. Cheers.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: By the way, you said you have a cough. I think I'm going to get it because I'm going to be drinking out of your glass all night.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: You know what? It was a beautiful day. Oh no, before we get to that, our kids are watching, Anderson.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: My kids, I told them they could watch the first ten minutes only.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I don't think -- I don't know if my kids are watching, but I hope they are.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I hope they are because what I want to do. Sorry, to everyone else who's watching.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Oh, you're not going to do like a wave.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I want to wave. Hey, Ben and Lucy, Happy New Year.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: We've become these people. We've become the people we used to mock.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: In life if any young people are watching at a certain point in life, you will become the people you used to make fun of. And that's what we've become.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I also just want to -- just take a moment before the whole program begins and before the rain begins, because it is supposed to rain.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Wow, I'm really feeling that tequila. It's like its emanating, it's like a warming --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: It's like bringing up -- wow, that's what tequila does, I don't know. I'm not sure where this is going --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: But I just wanted to say thank you. And not just on behalf of me because not a lot of people know this about, Andy, but he is a big activist. And when he takes a stand on something, I mean, he really takes a stand.Several years ago, Andy was on this stage pouring rain. We were not allowed to have umbrellas -- not allowed umbrellas because of the Times Square lines or whatever, there was a rule. It was a security rule, couldn't have umbrellas. I don't understand why. Maybe it was blocking people's view. We had transparent plastic umbrellas. I think we may have a clip. Andy went on a rant, no surprise, about the lack of umbrellas. Take a look. (BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: It's more than drizzling in Times Square. It's not putting a damper on anything, but I will say this. I had this umbrella. The lady from the Times Square Alliance came over and said, you have to get rid of the umbrella.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: This has been going on for an-hour-and-a-half all already.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Off the air and I said, I won't do it.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: He was like, what are you going to do, arrest me?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes, I go get the paddy wagon if that's what it's going to take. Now, they are threatening to pull CNN's spot from the credential, you know, from Times Square --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: -- for next year. This is some grade A BS, honestly.(END VIDEO CLIP)

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Well, because Andy Cohen, like the activist that he is, he made a stand and he changed the law.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Umbrellas are now allowed on the riser. So if it pours with rain, we will be allowed to have umbrellas. So, I just want to say thank you. COHEN

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And you're welcome, and all of you are welcome. Telemundo over here --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I was actually obligated -- Andy and his contract, he insisted I praise him for that.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes, somehow Seacrest always got an umbrella, but we can never have an umbrella.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I'm already scared. Oh, God. Don't start it.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: For now, anyway, listen, I have to say, we we're talking about, Anderson and I were looking back on the year.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: My highlight of the year, besides all the stuff I did with my kids, which I'm not going to bore you with, was going to Sphere in Las Vegas to see Dead and Company. This is --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Oh, great, you have the video, that's what you're laughing at? Have you guys seen this?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Someone videoed me dancing in a concert video. Having the best time of my life --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I'm not going to look at it. I lived it, man.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Oh my God, what are you --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Have you ever had fun? You ever had fun? No, this is sad.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: No, it's not sad. You are 56 years old, that is sad.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: You put me on last year.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: What are you even wearing? Are you wearing a circus tent?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Don't worry about it. I'm wearing very cool pants.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Where did you find that? Did you buy that in the parking lot outside?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: It look great, from Camp High, oh, Greg, okay.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Well, actually, okay -- all right, well, I'm sorry.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And the shirt was a gift from someone in the parking lot.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: But I mean, Sweetie, did you know you were being filmed?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: No, I didn't. I was at a concert, okay.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Again, to the young people watching, just always assume you're being filmed. This, I mean, Sweetie--

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Wow, were you really doing this?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes, I was feeling it. Have you ever had fun? Have you ever had fun?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I can't believe you did -- when I saw that online, I knew he was going to the show. He loves the show. It's so funny. I saw it online --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I didn't -- you never mentioned it to me.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I was so ashamed for you. And I can't believe you brought it up on TV as a good thing. I didn't know you were going to do that. That's why I'm so freaked out.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Talking about fun, we were going to do something fun.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: We're going to take our kids together to Disney.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And I am so excited. We are so indoctrinated into the whole --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I went to Disney for the first time. This is not like some Disney thing. I went to Disney when I was five years old. The first time I was away from my family. I went with Carter Burton --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Did Mickey Mouse, take you on a private plane?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I was so invulnerable, every night, I had to call like, my dad and my nanny every night and talk to them. And I was inconsolable, yes, very relatable.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes, your dad and your nanny. Do you know who the Big Five are?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: No. What characters are the Big Five in Disney?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes, although, you know what my daughter's favorite is Daisy Duck.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Oh, I'm not familiar with Daisy.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: She's not in the Big Five, look, Daisy Duck is Donald's girl. She's not in the Big Five, very limited sizing of Daisy Duck merch.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: At the store, I was at the Disney store last week. I'm starting a petition to get Daisy Duck in the Big Five.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I think, you know, again, with the activism. Thank you.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: It is time Dear Daisy Duck got her due.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I use my platform, yes, I do, Anderson. You are so nasty about me dancing at a concert.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I mean, I literally it is etched -- can we show it again? Can we just show it again?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: No, no. I am going to take you to a Dead show and you're going to dance.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes, I can't. Nothing against the Dead, but I just --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Okay, you don't need to play it again. We are good, wea re good.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: It is actually not sad. You're going to get really hazed online for your --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: This is -- by the way, this is what they call in 2024 a bad take.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes. This is a bad take.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Wow. You're trying to turn everybody down.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Do your thing, Internet. Are you for the guy having fun at a concert privately?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I felt the first drop of rain.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I did, too. I know. Where is that umbrella?Oh my gosh.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Anderson, did you have any fun this year?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I did, I had a lot of fun.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I got -- I hung out with -- I got to hang out with -- I got to meet Dua Lipa.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I did a piece on "60 Minutes" about her.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: And I really want to go see her in concert.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: She's got a big world tour.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Well, God forbid someone, you know, videos you having fun.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Well, I would hope -- no, I would be. I would hope not.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes. I want to go see the Scissor Sisters with -- I want to go see with you.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes. World tour. I interviewed Kevin Hart. That was fun as well.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes, I would like to see that. I would have liked to seen that as well.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Anderson, it is going to be a long night.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: It's going to be a really long night.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And also ahead, we have Jon Hamm is going to be joining us and helping us get the party started. The viral roller skaters, the Griffin Brothers, Marcus and Michael.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Less than four hours, the ball drop, Times Square. Getting more and more crowded. The crowds are starting to pick up.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I am going to go give them some tequila.Joining us now, the queen of entertaining on the biggest night for entertaining and the funniest person, I know, Amy Sedaris.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: She's also the sanest person in the room.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Always. I am always the sanest in the room.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: She is always the sanest person in the room?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: According to her, but I agree, I do agree.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I do agree actually.Amy, you look so great.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And I have to say, you've not only spent like, six of our seven New Year's Eve broadcasts here with us --

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: That's right. I am here every year. Thanks for having me.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: We did a weather report early on.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: I should and now, it is raining.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: But not only that, you and I have spent so many New Year's together.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: This morning on my memories. It is so crazy. This picture came up of us in 2004. We were pretending -- COOPER

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: This is us on New Year's Eve. We're pretending to be a married couple fighting on New Year's Eve.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: We look like a couple though, don't we.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Yes, that's when you were straight.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I was. As a matter of fact, I made love to you all night that night.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Bring a book. Bring a book to that book.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Amy, where are you headed after you get done with this?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: I am going back to my apartment. And I have a few friends that are there waiting for me.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Anyone you want to shout out?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Adam Selman. There are lots of people.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: So that's going to be a fun thing to walk into my apartment. So it will be fun to enter.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: The party will already be going on.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: You will not have had to deal with what I think is the most annoying part of parties, which is the very beginning, waiting for them to kind of lift off. Is that right?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Did you give out keys or they're already there?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: But you know what? I am going to tell you something new -- two new things in my life.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: I got an air purifier for the first time.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: And I had a little rash on my finger. Gone.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: And then I got a minimizer bra for those ladies out there who are full chested. I got a minimizer. Look how -- I look as flat as a board.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Do you want to look flat as a lady?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Yes. I'm too short to have --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: You know, that was the style in the 1920s, flat as a board.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Minimizer. Ladies, i highly recommend. It is fantastic.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Speaking of brassieres, you spent a good chunk of this year listening to Barbra Streisand's audiobook.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: It was gold. I would probably do it again.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: How long did it take you?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: It took two weeks. But it was like having a roommate who doesn't stop talking. But I didn't want her to stop talking. And so, like you, you paced it, you know?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: And that's what I did. And I used to imitate her when I was younger, I was obsessed. So it is just a different voice. It is just a little older and deeper. So I got to, you know -=-

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Can you do a little Barbra?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Oh, it's just a little bit more like this you know, like a down. More like the walnuts in the brownies instead of the walnuts in the brownies. You know, it is just a little deeper. Obsessed. You gave me a poster. You and Sarah Jessica Parker.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Amy, since you are always the sanest person in the room, we solicited for questions for you.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: You are the queen of hospitality. I know some queen had to make this box. I will tell you that much.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Anyway, okay, so we have a lot of questions for you.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: What fashion trend do you think should make a comeback in 2025?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Okay. What is your favorite cooking utensil and why?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Because I didn't always use tongs until recently, and I am like, wow, these are really handy.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Yes. I have tongs a lot as gifts.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: How do you handle a friend who is always canceling plans on you? Because this is me.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Yes, Sorry. That's a good question.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I ran out of party poppers for my New Year's Eve party. What should I do to celebrate instead?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: No party poppers. Not like poppers.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Well, my mind went right there. Can't you just bang on a pot?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Bang a pot with a wooden spoon.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Here is another one. My mother always says don't get her anything but then pouts when we listen to her and don't. What's the best gift for someone like that?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Oh, when they don't want something?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Give them -- if they say they don't want something, don't give them anything. That's just the rule.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: What's your favorite kind of gift to give someone you really don't know?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Parmesan cheese. Because it is a good thing to regift.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Oh, you can regift parmesan cheese.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I am hosting a birthday party for 12 three-year-olds. What should I put in the goodie bag?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I am single and still searching for the one. What green flags do you think I should be looking for as I date in the New Year?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Oh, that's a good question. I would find out what hair products they use, especially for men.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: I've been hearing a lot about hair products for men, to make their hair grow.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: What do you do if you're hosting a New Year's Eve party and you politely want to let everyone know it is time to leave.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: What should -- at what point should I take down my Christmas Tree?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Tomorrow. A lot of people leave it up. That's just my personal.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Oh, my God. It is so pretty.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: And even did my makeup. Yes, it was fun getting ready.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I don't want to mess it up.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: It is always fun getting ready to come here.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes, well we love having you.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: What's more fun? Coming or going?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: By the way, Amy and her brother David are going to be in my podcast next week.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: I want like you to just trash it.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Oh my gosh. No, it is so good.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Oh, I've laughed so hard. We thought you said weepy, not grieving.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Coming up, the one and only Jon Hamm joins us.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Later, music from Sting, Meghan Trainor and more as we count down to the New Year. It is raining.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: We are back in the glamorous Times Square.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: They are trying to torture us it seems. And you know what? Bring it on, everybody.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: You know what? 2024 was such a year.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
